R can overload weak devices.</li><li><strong>Offline Support</strong>: Requires service workers and often a CSR or SSG foundation with client-side caching.</li></ul><h4>Common Pitfall</h4><p>Over-engineering: Teams often default to SSR for every app without considering if SSG or CSR suffices. This adds unnecessary server cost and complexity. Always start with the simplest viable rendering pattern and scale up based on measured requirements.</p><h4>Production Relevance</h4><p>In production, the choice affects deployment (static hosting vs Node.js servers), caching strategies, and developer experience. A systematic requirements checklist (SEO, data freshness, device profile, offline needs) helps make an informed decision.</p>","diagramMermaid":"flowchart LR
    A[Requirements] --> B{SEO Needed?}
    B -->|Yes| C{Data Fresh?}
    B -->|No| D{Real-time?}
    C -->|Static| E[SSG]
    C -->|Dynamic| F[SSR]
    D -->|Yes| G[CSR]
    D -->|No| H[SSG or CSR]"}]

